\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 30.                 Haloxylon              }  Bunge
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By P.W. Ball.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Small shrubs with articulate stems. Leaves opposite, connate and amplexicaul, forming segments; lamina rudimentary. Inflorescence spicate, usually interrupted; flowers usually solitary. Perianth-segments 5, developing a transverse wing dorsally in fruit. Stamens usually 5, connate. Stigmas 4. Seeds horizontal.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. H. tamariscifolium} (L.) Pau,{\i  Bol. Soc. Aragon. Ci. Nat.}{\b  2:} 71 (1903) ({\i Haloxylon articulatum} (Moq.) Bunge,{\i  Hammada tamariscisolia} (L.) Iljin). Plant 10-60 cm, erect, caespitose, glaucous; segments of main branches c. 10 mm. Leaves with lamina up to 3 mm, triangular-subulate. Perianth-segments c. 1 mm, elliptical, obtuse; wing up to 3 × 4 mm, reniform-orbicular to orbicular-ovate, pinkish. {\i Dry saline soils. S.E. Spain.} Hs. ({\i N. Africa, S.W. Asia}.)
\par

