\pard\f0\fs28 Annual, usually pubescent herbs. Leaves alternate or opposite, cylindrical or semi-cylindrical. Inflorescence a panicle, the flowers hermaphrodite, solitary, axillary; bracteoles 2, becoming hard and enclosing the fruit. Perianth-segments 2-5. Stamens 1-5. Stigmas 2. Seeds vertical.
\par

